We got that
wheelchair kid inside.
We're gonna flip it.

663
00:39:20.258 --> 00:39:21.935
Isn't that kind of dangerous?

664
00:39:21.959 --> 00:39:23.743
He's already in a wheelchair.

665
00:39:23.812 --> 00:39:26.412
Come on. dude.
We saved you the first roll.

666
00:39:29.133 --> 00:39:31.567
Oh!

667
00:39:31.636 --> 00:39:33.986
Thank you. Thank you so much.

668
00:39:35.306 --> 00:39:37.740
Thank you.
Oh. my God. The smell.

669
00:39:37.809 --> 00:39:40.927
What the hell. dude?
I can't believe you're
helping out this loser.

670
00:39:40.996 --> 00:39:44.730
Don't you get it. man?
We're all losers.

671
00:39:44.799 --> 00:39:46.616
<i>Everyone in this school.</i>

672
00:39:46.685 --> 00:39:49.368
Hell. everyone in this town.

673
00:39:49.437 --> 00:39:52.483
Out of all the kids
who graduate. maybe half
will go to college.

674
00:39:52.507 --> 00:39:55.174
And... And two will leave
the state to do it.

675
00:39:55.242 --> 00:39:59.445
I'm not afraid of being
called a loser. 'cause I can
accept that that's what I am.

676
00:40:00.748 --> 00:40:03.227
But I am afraid
of turning my back
on something...

677
00:40:03.251 --> 00:40:06.085
that actually made me happy
for the first time
in my sorry life.

678
00:40:06.154 --> 00:40:09.271
So. what? Are you quitting
to join Homo Explosion?

679
00:40:09.340 --> 00:40:11.775
No. I'm doing both.

680
00:40:11.843 --> 00:40:14.989
<i>'Cause you can't</i>
<i>win without me.</i>
<i>and neither can they.</i>

681
00:40:21.035 --> 00:40:24.103
